itunesNotes.standard: This user-friendly design app makes it fun turning photos into gorgeous graphic art. With Over you’ll add exquisitely styled text, shapes and clip art to your images, all in a powerful interface you can control with your thumb. Just tap to select elements, then swipe to change colours, fonts, spacing—even nudge objects for pixel-perfect layouts. Over is flexible too, letting you customise its tools and features as your imagination grows.

itunesNotes.short: Advanced auto-enhance tools and sophisticated filters to edit every detail of your photo.
itunesNotes.standard: Plenty of photo-editing apps come with filters, but Polarr can help you create your own. And you don’t need the eye of a professional photographer, either. Thanks to instinctive touch controls and a ton of built-in filters to use as jumping-off points, it’s simple to tweak your images to get the perfect balance of colour and light. For the shutterbug pros, Polarr goes deep and allows fine adjustments to saturation, lens distortion and a whole lot of other settings that we dabblers just pretend to understand.

itunesNotes.standard: Pixelmator sets a new standard for photo editing on iPhone and iPad with a suite of staggeringly powerful tools. Combining gorgeous templates, intuitive touch-screen controls and completely customisable effects, this full-featured editor is in a class all its own. Plus, with seamless syncing using iCloud Drive, it doesn’t matter where the project was started—you can keep editing on your iPhone, iPad or Mac.

itunesNotes.short: Turn your photo into a masterpiece with this powerful app.
itunesNotes.standard: Enlight proves that powerful photo editing isn’t just for pros. Packed with an unprecedented variety of tools, this Apple Design Award winner smoothly handles everything from quick tweaks to creating that double-exposure masterpiece. Expertly crafted presets give you vast creative options, and if you want to go deeper, you’ll find everything from oil painting and universal masking to advanced tonal and colour adjustments.

itunesNotes.standard: From its humble origin as a fun way to send self-erasing photo messages, Snapchat has grown into one of our favourite social media apps. And not just for the hilarious face filters and cool geographical photo tags. It’s become one of the best ways to share memories, maintain friendships and stay up to date on news and views from our go-to websites.

itunesNotes.standard: Ready to unleash your cartoon alter ego? CHOMP takes your face and sticks it on dozens of interactive animations, letting you instantly record the bizarre and hilarious results.
